//// Integrate Apache Kafka with a Spring Boot application to send and receive messages.
we'll walk through the steps of setting up Kafka, adding dependencies, and implementing a producer and consumer.

steps or prerequisites:
1) first step for setting up the kafka is
    download and install the kafka in your system
    --> i have downloaded the
        4.1.1
        Released November 12, 2025
        Release Notes
        Docker image: apache/kafka:4.1.1.
        Docker Native image: apache/kafka-native:4.1.1.
        Source download: kafka-4.1.1-src.tgz (asc, sha512)
        Binary download: kafka_2.13-4.1.1.tgz (asc, sha512)

        this binary download and extracted the .tgz to c:\kafka
    --> after downloading we need to extract that binary folder into c:\kafka using winrar
    ---> we have to make some keyy difference in kafka
    ---> for kafka version 3> we have zookeeper configuration external
    ---> but for the kafka version 3+ we dont need the zookeeper configuration


    ===> BUT WE MUST VERIFY SOME CONFIGURATION INSIDE THE SERVER.PROPERTIES
         Check the server.properties file shown in your screenshot (at the bottom of the list).
         In Kafka 4.x, this file typically contains the KRaft-specific settings like process.roles, node.id, and controller.quorum.voters by default.
         Open C:\kafka\kafka_2.13-4.1.1\config\server.properties in a text editor.

         Ensure it contains these KRaft settings:
         process.roles=broker,controller
         node.id=1
         controller.quorum.voters=1@localhost:9093

         Crucial for Windows: Change the log directory to a Windows path:
         Find: log.dirs=/tmp/kafka-logs
         Change to: log.dirs=C:/kafka/data/kafka-logs (use forward slashes /).

         WE HAVE TO MANUALLY CREATE A NEW FOLDER INSIDE THE C:\KAFKA WHICH IS DATA BEFORE ADDING THE ABOVE CONFIGURATION
         FOR LOGGING
2) after setting and configuring the kafka server
    we have to go to cmd and run the below commands
    >>>>>C:\kafka\kafka_2.13-4.1.1>.\bin\windows\kafka-storage.bat random-uuid (( CRUCIAL FOR SETUP TO WORK))
    2025-12-17T12:35:55.688555Z main ERROR Reconfiguration failed: No configuration found for '764c12b6' at 'null' in 'null'
    Sw36lFZ-SYiNQN3g2jlrfA

    ?????C:\kafka\kafka_2.13-4.1.1>.\bin\windows\kafka-storage.bat format -t Sw36lFZ-SYiNQN3g2jlrfA -c .\config\server.properties
    2025-12-17T12:36:58.236364700Z main ERROR Reconfiguration failed: No configuration found for '764c12b6' at 'null' in 'null'
    Because controller.quorum.voters is not set on this controller, you must specify one of the following: --standalone, --initial-controllers, or --no-initial-controllers.

    >>>>>C:\kafka\kafka_2.13-4.1.1>.\bin\windows\kafka-storage.bat format --standalone -t Sw36lFZ-SYiNQN3g2jlrfA -c .\config\server.properties
    2025-12-17T12:37:44.320717200Z main ERROR Reconfiguration failed: No configuration found for '764c12b6' at 'null' in 'null'
    Formatting dynamic metadata voter directory C:/kafka/data/kraft-combined-logs with metadata.version 4.1-IV1.

    C:\kafka\kafka_2.13-4.1.1>.\bin\windows\kafka-server-start.bat .\config\server.properties

    // THIS LAST CMD IS FOR RUNNING THE KAFKA SERVER IN YOUR LOCAL SYSTEM
       and at that path only.....
       this particular kafka server will be running in the http://localhost:9092



    // for the ACTUAL SPRINGBOOT INTEGRATION we need the following dependencies
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-kafka</artifactId>
    </dependency>

    by this we can able to publish and subscribe to events via kafka

    //// CRUCIAL FOR KAFKA
         WE ALSO NEED THE
         <!--         WE NEED THE JACKSON DATA BIND JAR FOR MAKING THE SERIALIZATION AND DESERIALIZATION ACTUALLY WORK-->
         <!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/com.fasterxml.jackson.core/jackson-databind -->
         <dependency>
             <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.core</groupId>
             <artifactId>jackson-databind</artifactId>
             <version>2.20.1</version>
         </dependency>

     THIS IS ACTUALLY NOT PROVIDED IN THE INTELLIJ ULTIMATE DEPENDENCIES FOR MODULE MAVEN

     // SO GO TO THE ACTUAL MAVEN REPOSITORY AND COPY THIS DEPENDENCY FROM THERE